      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA software used under a documented quality management system with version control and regression testing.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2021 R2 was operated under an FDA-recognized QMS. Version control logs and regression test suite results are archived. Required gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems with analytical solutions demonstrate correct implementation of element formulations and contact algorithms.",
      "rationale": "Three NAFEMS benchmark cases and two Hertzian contact problems were solved; all results within 1% of analytical reference. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change less than 5% between successive refinements; GCI reported.",
      "rationale": "Four-level mesh refinement study performed on the screw-rod junction region. GCI for stiffness QoI is 2.1%; failure load GCI is 3.4%. Both below 5% threshold. Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals and energy balance errors reported and within solver tolerance for all load steps.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson residual norms converged to 1e-6 for all 132 load increments across 11 constructs. Energy balance error < 0.01%. Gradation 2 met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation protocol reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition setup verified against ASTM F1717 test fixture geometry.",
      "rationale": "A secondary analyst independently reconstructed boundary conditions from the simulation protocol and compared nodal constraints against the physical fixture CAD. No discrepancies found. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model selection justified by material characterization data; contact formulation validated against known interface behavior.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V modeled as isotropic linear elastic; justified by uniaxial coupon data showing elastic regime dominates under F1717 loading. Augmented Lagrangian contact validated against Hertz benchmarks. Gradation 3 met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs sourced from traceable measurements with uncertainty bounds reported.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa ± 2%) and Poisson ratio (0.342 ± 0.5%) from certified coupon testing. Screw geometry from CMM measurements of production lot (n=5). Input uncertainty propagated via Latin hypercube sampling. Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 experimental constructs from production-representative lot; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to design specification.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs drawn from a single production lot; CMM inspection of all 11 confirmed dimensional conformance within drawing tolerances. Two independent laboratories each tested a subset. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios including at least two axial load levels and two moment arm configurations.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single axial preload (400 N) and single moment arm (100 mm) per ASTM F1717 standard configuration. Variation across loading scenarios was not evaluated. Achieved gradation 2 falls below required gradation 3; accepted as residual gap with documented rationale in decision record."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs (geometry, material, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to experimental test article and setup within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FEA geometry derived from CMM data of the same production lot used in testing. Boundary conditions replicate fixture kinematics verified by lab fixture drawings. Torque preload on screw-rod interface matched to experimental torque wrench records. Gradation 3 met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., MAPE, Sprague-Geers) applied; simulation predictions fall within experimental variability band.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute percentage error for stiffness: 4.2% (experimental CV=6.1%). Sprague-Geers magnitude metric M=0.03, phase metric P=0.01. All 11 construct stiffness predictions within ±1 experimental standard deviation. Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs predicted by the model (stiffness, failure load) are directly linked to the decision-relevant performance endpoints stated in the device requirement.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and failure load under compression-bending are the primary mechanical performance endpoints in the 510(k) substantial equivalence argument for this Class II device. The binding requirement node explicitly states these as decision-relevant QoIs. Gradation 3 met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario (ASTM F1717 bench test) is sufficiently representative of the intended clinical loading environment and device configuration described in the claim.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 is the FDA-recognized consensus standard for spinal implant mechanical testing and is accepted as the relevant validation scenario for pedicle screw constructs in the 510(k) pathway. Device configuration (7.5 mm non-cannulated screw, titanium rod) matches the claim scope. Gradation 3 satisfied."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted-2026-04-19",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single shortfall — Test Conditions falling at gradation 2 against a required gradation 3 — reflects the constraint of the ASTM F1717 standard to a single canonical load configuration, which is the regulatory norm for this device class. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support a Medium model risk level decision for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending FEA prediction. Assessment accepted with the Test Conditions gap documented.",
